-- Marsh & McLennan Outlook Lifted by S&P on Operating Results
-- B y   L a u r a   M a r c i n e k
-- 2013-06-21T18:46:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-21/marsh-mclennan-outlook-lifted-by-s-p-on-operating-results.html
Marsh & McLennan Cos., the largest
insurance broker by market value, had its outlook raised by
 Standard & Poor’s  as financial results improve.  The outlook was raised to positive from stable on the
“continued trajectory of improved operating performance over
the past year,” the ratings firm said today in a statement on
the New York-based company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Marcinek in New York at 
 Lmarcinek3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
